#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:1
msgid "Additional Python Wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:3
msgid "Python wheels for VTK are available in pypi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:5
msgid "pip install vtk\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:9
msgid ""
"More wheels can be accessed from the [GitLab Package Registry](https://"
"gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/packages)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:11
msgid "To install the **latest release** wheel from the GitLab registry:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:13
msgid "pip install --extra-index-url https://wheels.vtk.org vtk\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:17
msgid "To install the latest wheel **from master**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:19
msgid ""
"pip install --extra-index-url https://wheels.vtk.org vtk --pre --no-cache\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:23
msgid ""
"The wheels available at PyPi are built using the default rendering backend "
"which leverages any available hardware graphics for generating the scene. "
"There is also a OSMesa wheel variant that leverages offscreen rendering with "
"OSMesa. This wheel is being built for both Linux and Windows at this time "
"and bundles all of the necessary libraries into the wheel. These wheels are "
"intended to be used by downstream projects in headless, CI-like environments "
"or cloud application deployments, preventing the need to install any "
"addition system packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:33
msgid ""
"As of VTK 9.4, OSMesa and EGL support are included by default in the `vtk` "
"wheels and can be selected at runtime. The `vtk-osmesa` wheels are no longer "
"provided, and it is no longer necessary to install `vtk-osmesa`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:37
msgid ""
"conda-forge packages are also [available](https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/"
"vtk) and maintained by the community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:40
msgid "VTK wheel SDKs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/available_python_wheels.md:42
msgid ""
"VTK wheel SDKs can be accessed from the [GitLab Package Registry](https://"
"gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/packages). For more information about the VTK "
"wheel SDKs, please refer to [Wheel SDKs section](wheel_sdks)."
msgstr ""
